WhitespaceMinimizedString.name: WhitespaceMinimizedString
WhitespaceMinimizedString.description: A string that has all whitespace trimmed off of beginning and end, and all internal whitespace segments reduced to single spaces. Whitespace includes #x9 (tab), #xA (linefeed), and #xD (carriage return).

Provenance.name: Provenance
Provenance.description: A field containing a DataHarmonizer versioning marker. It is issued by DataHarmonizer when validation is applied to a given row of data.

float.name: float
float.description: A real number that conforms to the xsd:float specification

double.name: double
double.description: A real number that conforms to the xsd:double specification

decimal.name: decimal
decimal.description: A real number with arbitrary precision that conforms to the xsd:decimal specification

time.name: time
time.description: A time object represents a (local) time of day, independent of any particular day
notes: URI is dateTime because OWL reasoners do not work with straight date or time

date.name: date
date.description: a date (year, month and day) in an idealized calendar
notes: URI is dateTime because OWL reasoners don't work with straight date or time

datetime.name: datetime
datetime.description: The combination of a date and time

date_or_datetime.name: date_or_datetime
date_or_datetime.description: Either a date or a datetime

curie.name: curie
comments: in RDF serializations this MUST be expanded to a URI
in non-RDF serializations MAY be serialized as the compact representation

uri.name: uri

objectidentifier.name: objectidentifier
objectidentifier.description: A URI or CURIE that represents an object in the model.
comments: Used for inheritence and type checking

nodeidentifier.name: nodeidentifier
nodeidentifier.description: A URI, CURIE or BNODE that represents a node in a model.

specimen collector sample ID.name: specimen collector sample ID
specimen collector sample ID.description: The user-defined name for the sample.
specimen collector sample ID.title: specimen collector sample ID
comments: Store the collector sample ID. If this number is considered identifiable information, provide an alternative ID. Be sure to store the key that maps between the original and alternative IDs for traceability and follow up if necessary. Every collector sample ID from a single submitter must be unique. It can have any format, but we suggest that you make it concise, unique and consistent within your lab.
exact_mappings: GISAID:Sample ID given by the sample provider

third party lab service provider name.name: third party lab service provider name
third party lab service provider name.description: The name of the third party company or laboratory that provided services.
third party lab service provider name.title: third party lab service provider name
comments: Provide the full, unabbreviated name of the company or laboratory.

third party lab sample ID.name: third party lab sample ID
third party lab sample ID.description: The identifier assigned to a sample by a third party service provider.
third party lab sample ID.title: third party lab sample ID
comments: Store the sample identifier supplied by the third party services provider.

case ID.name: case ID
case ID.description: The identifier used to specify an epidemiologically detected case of disease.
case ID.title: case ID
comments: Provide the case identifer. The case ID greatly facilitates linkage between laboratory and epidemiological data. The case ID may be considered identifiable information. Consult the data steward before sharing.

Related specimen primary ID.name: Related specimen primary ID
Related specimen primary ID.description: The primary ID of a related specimen previously submitted to the repository.
Related specimen primary ID.title: Related specimen primary ID
comments: Store the primary ID of the related specimen previously submitted to the National Microbiology Laboratory so that the samples can be linked and tracked through the system.

IRIDA sample name.name: IRIDA sample name
IRIDA sample name.description: The identifier assigned to a sequenced isolate in IRIDA.
IRIDA sample name.title: IRIDA sample name
comments: Store the IRIDA sample name. The IRIDA sample name will be created by the individual entering data into the IRIDA platform. IRIDA samples may be linked to metadata and sequence data, or just metadata alone. It is recommended that the IRIDA sample name be the same as, or contain, the specimen collector sample ID for better traceability. It is also recommended that the IRIDA sample name mirror the GISAID accession. IRIDA sample names cannot contain slashes. Slashes should be replaced by underscores. See IRIDA documentation for more information regarding special characters (https://irida.corefacility.ca/documentation/user/user/samples/#adding-a-new-sample).

umbrella bioproject accession.name: umbrella bioproject accession
umbrella bioproject accession.description: The INSDC accession number assigned to the umbrella BioProject.
umbrella bioproject accession.title: umbrella bioproject accession
comments: Store the umbrella BioProject accession by selecting it from the picklist in the template. The umbrella BioProject accession will be identical for all CanCOGen submitters. Different provinces will have their own BioProjects, however these BioProjects will be linked under one umbrella BioProject.

bioproject accession.name: bioproject accession
bioproject accession.description: The INSDC accession number of the BioProject(s) to which the BioSample belongs.
bioproject accession.title: bioproject accession
comments: Store the BioProject accession number. BioProjects are an organizing tool that links together raw sequence data, assemblies, and their associated metadata. Each province will be assigned a different bioproject accession number by the National Microbiology Lab. A valid NCBI BioProject accession has prefix PRJN e.g., PRJNA12345, and is created once at the beginning of a new sequencing project.

biosample accession.name: biosample accession
biosample accession.description: The identifier assigned to a BioSample in INSDC archives.
biosample accession.title: biosample accession
comments: Store the accession returned from the BioSample submission. NCBI BioSamples will have the prefix SAMN.

SRA accession.name: SRA accession
SRA accession.description: The Sequence Read Archive (SRA) identifier linking raw read data, methodological metadata and quality control metrics submitted to the INSDC.
SRA accession.title: SRA accession
comments: Store the accession assigned to the submitted "run". NCBI-SRA accessions start with SRR.

GenBank accession.name: GenBank accession
GenBank accession.description: The GenBank identifier assigned to the sequence in the INSDC archives.
GenBank accession.title: GenBank accession
comments: Store the accession returned from a GenBank submission (viral genome assembly).

GISAID accession.name: GISAID accession
GISAID accession.description: The GISAID accession number assigned to the sequence.
GISAID accession.title: GISAID accession
comments: Store the accession returned from the GISAID submission.

GISAID virus name.name: GISAID virus name
GISAID virus name.description: The user-defined name of the virus, specified in the organism-specific format prescribed by the GISAID database.
GISAID virus name.title: GISAID virus name
comments: Provide the GISAID virus name, which should be written in the format: A/Province/Country/SampleID/year

sample collected by.name: sample collected by
sample collected by.description: The name of the agency that collected the original sample.
sample collected by.title: sample collected by
comments: The name of the sample collector should be written out in full, (with minor exceptions) and be consistent across multple submissions e.g. Public Health Agency of Canada, Public Health Ontario, BC Centre for Disease Control. The sample collector specified is at the discretion of the data provider (i.e. may be hospital, provincial public health lab, or other).

sample collector contact email.name: sample collector contact email
sample collector contact email.description: The email address of the contact responsible for follow-up regarding the sample.
sample collector contact email.title: sample collector contact email
comments: The email address can represent a specific individual or lab e.g. johnnyblogs@lab.ca, or RespLab@lab.ca

sequenced by.name: sequenced by
sequenced by.description: The name of the agency that generated the sequence.
sequenced by.title: sequenced by
comments: The name of the agency should be written out in full, (with minor exceptions) and be consistent across multiple submissions. If submitting specimens rather than sequencing data, please put the "National Microbiology Laboratory (NML)".

sequence submitted by.name: sequence submitted by
sequence submitted by.description: The name of the agency that generated the sequence.
sequence submitted by.title: sequence submitted by
comments: The name of the agency should be written out in full, (with minor exceptions) and be consistent across multple submissions. If submitting specimens rather than sequencing data, please put the "National Microbiology Laboratory (NML)".

sample collection date.name: sample collection date
sample collection date.description: The date on which the sample was collected.
sample collection date.title: sample collection date
comments: Sample collection date is critical for surveillance and many types of analyses. Required granularity includes year, month and day. If this date is considered identifiable information, it is acceptable to add "jitter" by adding or subtracting a calendar day (acceptable by GISAID). Alternatively, received date may be used as a substitute. The date should be provided in ISO 8601 standard format "YYYY-MM-DD".

sample collection date precision.name: sample collection date precision
sample collection date precision.description: The precision to which the "sample collection date" was provided.
sample collection date precision.title: sample collection date precision
comments: Provide the precision of granularity to the "day", "month", or "year" for the date provided in the "sample collection date" field. The "sample collection date" will be truncated to the precision specified upon export; "day" for "YYYY-MM-DD", "month" for "YYYY-MM", or "year" for "YYYY".

geo_loc_name (country).name: geo_loc_name (country)
geo_loc_name (country).description: The country where the sample was collected.
geo_loc_name (country).title: geo_loc_name (country)
comments: Provide the country name from the controlled vocabulary provided.

geo_loc_name (state/province/territory).name: geo_loc_name (state/province/territory)
geo_loc_name (state/province/territory).description: The province/territory where the sample was collected.
geo_loc_name (state/province/territory).title: geo_loc_name (state/province/territory)
comments: Provide the province/territory name from the controlled vocabulary provided.

organism.name: organism
organism.title: organism
comments: Select the type of influenza virus from the picklist provided.

purpose of sampling.name: purpose of sampling
purpose of sampling.description: The reason that the sample was collected.
purpose of sampling.title: purpose of sampling
comments: The reason a sample was collected may provide information about potential biases in sampling strategy. Provide the purpose of sampling from the picklist in the template. Most likely, the sample was collected for Diagnostic testing. The reason why a sample was originally collected may differ from the reason why it was selected for sequencing, which should be indicated in the "purpose of sequencing" field.

purpose of sampling details.name: purpose of sampling details
purpose of sampling details.description: The description of why the sample was collected, providing specific details.
purpose of sampling details.title: purpose of sampling details
comments: Provide an expanded description of why the sample was collected using free text. The description may include the importance of the sample for a particular public health investigation/surveillance activity/research question. If details are not available, provide a null value.

examples.value: The sample was collected to investigate the prevalence of variants associated with mink-to-human transmission in Canada.

exact_mappings: CNPHI:Details on the Reason for Sampling

NML submitted specimen type.name: NML submitted specimen type
NML submitted specimen type.description: The type of specimen submitted to the National Microbiology Laboratory (NML) for testing.
NML submitted specimen type.title: NML submitted specimen type
comments: This information is required for upload through the CNPHI LaSER system. Select the specimen type from the pick list provided. If sequence data is being submitted rather than a specimen for testing, select Not Applicable.

Related specimen relationship type.name: Related specimen relationship type
Related specimen relationship type.description: The relationship of the current specimen to the specimen/sample previously submitted to the repository.
Related specimen relationship type.title: Related specimen relationship type
comments: Provide the tag that describes how the previous sample is related to the current sample being submitted from the pick list provided, so that the samples can be linked and tracked in the system.

presampling_activity.name: presampling_activity
presampling_activity.description: The upstream activities or variables that may affect the sample collected.
presampling_activity.title: presampling_activity
comments: If there was an activity that would affect the sample prior to collection (this is different than sample processing), provide the activities by selecting one or more values from the template pick list. If the information is unknown or cannot be provided, leave blank or provide a null value.

presampling activity details.name: presampling activity details
presampling activity details.description: The details of the activities or variables that may affect the sample collected.
presampling activity details.title: presampling activity details
comments: Briefly describe the presampling details using free text.

examples.value: Patient was previously infected. Sample taken during convalescence.

anatomical material.name: anatomical material
anatomical material.description: A substance obtained from an anatomical part of an organism e.g. tissue, blood.
anatomical material.title: anatomical material
comments: Provide a descriptor if an anatomical material was sampled. Use the picklist provided in the template. If a desired term is missing from the picklist, contact emma_griffiths@sfu.ca. If not applicable, do not leave blank. Choose a null value.

anatomical part.name: anatomical part
anatomical part.description: An anatomical part of an organism e.g. oropharynx.
anatomical part.title: anatomical part
comments: Provide a descriptor if an anatomical part was sampled. Use the picklist provided in the template. If a desired term is missing from the picklist, contact emma_griffiths@sfu.ca. If not applicable, do not leave blank. Choose a null value.

body product.name: body product
body product.description: A substance excreted/secreted from an organism e.g. feces, urine, sweat.
body product.title: body product
comments: Provide a descriptor if a body product was sampled. Use the picklist provided in the template.  If a desired term is missing from the picklist, contact emma_griffiths@sfu.ca. If not applicable, do not leave blank. Choose a null value.

collection device.name: collection device
collection device.description: The instrument or container used to collect the sample e.g. swab.
collection device.title: collection device
comments: Provide a descriptor if a device was used for sampling. Use the picklist provided in the template. If a desired term is missing from the picklist, contact emma_griffiths@sfu.ca. If not applicable, do not leave blank. Choose a null value.

collection method.name: collection method
collection method.description: The process used to collect the sample e.g. phlebotamy, necropsy.
collection method.title: collection method
comments: Provide a descriptor if a collection method was used for sampling. Use the picklist provided in the template.  If a desired term is missing from the picklist, contact emma_griffiths@sfu.ca. If not applicable, do not leave blank. Choose a null value.

collection protocol.name: collection protocol
collection protocol.description: The name and version of a particular protocol used for sampling.
collection protocol.title: collection protocol
comments: Free text.

specimen processing.name: specimen processing
specimen processing.description: Any processing applied to the sample during or after receiving the sample.
specimen processing.title: specimen processing
comments: Critical for interpreting data. Select all the applicable processes from the pick list. If virus was passaged, include information in "lab host", "passage number", and "passage method" fields. If none of the processes in the pick list apply, put "not applicable".

specimen processing details.name: specimen processing details
specimen processing details.description: Detailed information regarding the processing applied to a sample during or after receiving the sample.
specimen processing details.title: specimen processing details
comments: Provide a free text description of any processing details applied to a sample.

examples.value: 25 swabs were pooled and further prepared as a single sample during library prep.

biomaterial extracted.name: biomaterial extracted
biomaterial extracted.description: The biomaterial extracted from samples for the purpose of sequencing.
biomaterial extracted.title: biomaterial extracted
comments: Provide the biomaterial extracted from the picklist in the template.

host (common name).name: host (common name)
host (common name).description: The commonly used name of the host.
host (common name).title: host (common name)
comments: Common name or scientific name are required if there was a host. Both can be provided, if known. Use terms from the pick lists in the template. Common name e.g. human, bat. If the sample was environmental, put "not applicable.

host (scientific name).name: host (scientific name)
host (scientific name).description: The taxonomic, or scientific name of the host.
host (scientific name).title: host (scientific name)
comments: Common name or scientific name are required if there was a host. Both can be provided, if known. Use terms from the pick lists in the template. Scientific name e.g. Homo sapiens, If the sample was environmental, put "not applicable

host health state.name: host health state
host health state.description: Health status of the host at the time of sample collection.
host health state.title: host health state
comments: If known, select a descriptor from the pick list provided in the template.

host health status details.name: host health status details
host health status details.description: Further details pertaining to the health or disease status of the host at time of collection.
host health status details.title: host health status details
comments: If known, select a descriptor from the pick list provided in the template.

host health outcome.name: host health outcome
host health outcome.title: host health outcome
comments: If known, select a descriptor from the pick list provided in the template.

host disease.name: host disease
host disease.description: The name of the disease experienced by the host.
host disease.title: host disease
comments: Select "Influenza" from the pick list provided in the template.

host age.name: host age
host age.description: Age of host at the time of sampling.
host age.title: host age
comments: Enter the age of the host in years. If not available, provide a null value. If there is not host, put "Not Applicable".

host age unit.name: host age unit
host age unit.description: The unit used to measure the host age, in either months or years.
host age unit.title: host age unit
comments: Indicate whether the host age is in months or years. Age indicated in months will be binned to the 0 - 9 year age bin.

host age bin.name: host age bin
host age bin.description: Age of host at the time of sampling, expressed as an age group.
host age bin.title: host age bin
comments: Select the corresponding host age bin from the pick list provided in the template. If not available, provide a null value.

host gender.name: host gender
host gender.description: The gender of the host at the time of sample collection.
host gender.title: host gender
comments: Select the corresponding host gender from the pick list provided in the template. If not available, provide a null value. If there is no host, put "Not Applicable".

host subject ID.name: host subject ID
host subject ID.description: A unique identifier by which each host can be referred to e.g. #131
host subject ID.title: host subject ID
comments: Provide the host identifier. Should be a unique, user-defined identifier.

host vaccination status.name: host vaccination status
host vaccination status.description: The vaccination status of the host (fully vaccinated, partially vaccinated, or not vaccinated).
host vaccination status.title: host vaccination status
comments: Select the vaccination status of the host from the pick list.

vaccination history.name: vaccination history
vaccination history.description: A description of the vaccines received and the administration dates of a series of vaccinations against a specific disease or a set of diseases.
vaccination history.title: vaccination history
comments: Free text description of the dates and vaccines administered against a particular disease/set of diseases. It is also acceptable to concatenate the individual dose information (vaccine name, vaccination date) separated by semicolons.

exposure event.name: exposure event
exposure event.title: exposure event
comments: Select an exposure event from the pick list provided in the template. If the desired term is missing, contact the curation team.

exposure contact level.name: exposure contact level
exposure contact level.title: exposure contact level
comments: Select direct or indirect exposure from the pick-list.

host role.name: host role
host role.description: The role of the host in relation to the exposure setting.
host role.title: host role
comments: Select the host's personal role(s) from the pick list provided in the template. If the desired term is missing, contact the curation team.

exposure setting.name: exposure setting
exposure setting.title: exposure setting
comments: Select the host exposure setting(s) from the pick list provided in the template. If a desired term is missing, contact the curation team.

exposure details.name: exposure details
exposure details.title: exposure details
comments: Free text description of the exposure.

purpose of sequencing.name: purpose of sequencing
purpose of sequencing.description: The reason that the sample was sequenced.
purpose of sequencing.title: purpose of sequencing
comments: The reason why a sample was originally collected may differ from the reason why it was selected for sequencing. The reason a sample was sequenced may provide information about potential biases in sequencing strategy. Provide the purpose of sequencing from the picklist in the template. The reason for sample collection should be indicated in the "purpose of sampling" field.

purpose of sequencing details.name: purpose of sequencing details
purpose of sequencing details.description: The description of why the sample was sequenced providing specific details.
purpose of sequencing details.title: purpose of sequencing details
comments: Provide an expanded description of why the sample was sequenced using free text. The description may include the importance of the sequences for a particular public health investigation/surveillance activity/research question. Suggested standardized descriotions include: Screened for S gene target failure (S dropout), Screened for mink variants, Screened for B.1.1.7 variant, Screened for B.1.135 variant, Screened for P.1 variant, Screened due to travel history, Screened due to close contact with infected individual, Assessing public health control measures, Determining early introductions and spread, Investigating airline-related exposures, Investigating temporary foreign worker, Investigating remote regions, Investigating health care workers, Investigating schools/universities, Investigating reinfection.
exact_mappings: CNPHI:Details on the Reason for Sequencing

sequencing date.name: sequencing date
sequencing date.description: The date the sample was sequenced.
sequencing date.title: sequencing date
comments: ISO 8601 standard "YYYY-MM-DD".

amplicon size.name: amplicon size
amplicon size.description: The length of the amplicon generated by PCR amplification.
amplicon size.title: amplicon size
comments: Provide the amplicon size, including the units.

library preparation kit.name: library preparation kit
library preparation kit.description: The name of the DNA library preparation kit used to generate the library being sequenced.
library preparation kit.title: library preparation kit
comments: Provide the name of the library preparation kit used.

sequencing instrument.name: sequencing instrument
sequencing instrument.description: The model of the sequencing instrument used.
sequencing instrument.title: sequencing instrument
comments: Select a sequencing instrument from the picklist provided in the template.

sequencing protocol.name: sequencing protocol
sequencing protocol.description: The protocol used to generate the sequence.
sequencing protocol.title: sequencing protocol
comments: Provide a free text description of the methods and materials used to generate the sequence. Suggested text, fill in information where indicated.: "Viral sequencing was performed following a tiling amplicon strategy using the <fill in> primer scheme. Sequencing was performed using a <fill in> sequencing instrument. Libraries were prepared using <fill in> library kit. "

examples.value: Genomes were generated through amplicon sequencing of 300 bp amplicons with ARTIC schema primers. Libraries were created using Illumina DNA Prep kits, and sequence data was produced using Miseq Micro v2 (500 cycles) sequencing kits.

amplicon pcr primer scheme.name: amplicon pcr primer scheme
amplicon pcr primer scheme.description: The specifications of the primers (primer sequences, binding positions, fragment size generated etc) used to generate the amplicons to be sequenced.
amplicon pcr primer scheme.title: amplicon pcr primer scheme
comments: Provide the name and version of the primer scheme used to generate the amplicons for sequencing.

raw sequence data processing method.name: raw sequence data processing method
raw sequence data processing method.description: The names of the software and version number used for raw data processing such as removing barcodes, adapter trimming, filtering etc.
raw sequence data processing method.title: raw sequence data processing method
comments: Provide the software name followed by the version e.g. Trimmomatic v. 0.38, Porechop v. 0.2.3

dehosting method.name: dehosting method
dehosting method.description: The method used to remove host reads from the pathogen sequence.
dehosting method.title: dehosting method
comments: Provide the name and version number of the software used to remove host reads.

consensus sequence software name.name: consensus sequence software name
consensus sequence software name.description: The name of software used to generate the consensus sequence.
consensus sequence software name.title: consensus sequence software name
comments: Provide the name of the software used to generate the consensus sequence.

consensus sequence software version.name: consensus sequence software version
consensus sequence software version.description: The version of the software used to generate the consensus sequence.
consensus sequence software version.title: consensus sequence software version
comments: Provide the version of the software used to generate the consensus sequence.

breadth of coverage value.name: breadth of coverage value
breadth of coverage value.description: The percentage of the reference genome covered by the sequenced data, to a prescribed depth.
breadth of coverage value.title: breadth of coverage value
comments: Provide value as a percent.

depth of coverage value.name: depth of coverage value
depth of coverage value.description: The average number of reads representing a given nucleotide in the reconstructed sequence.
depth of coverage value.title: depth of coverage value
comments: Provide value as a fold of coverage.

depth of coverage threshold.name: depth of coverage threshold
depth of coverage threshold.description: The threshold used as a cut-off for the depth of coverage.
depth of coverage threshold.title: depth of coverage threshold
comments: Provide the threshold fold coverage.

number of base pairs sequenced.name: number of base pairs sequenced
number of base pairs sequenced.description: The number of total base pairs generated by the sequencing process.
number of base pairs sequenced.title: number of base pairs sequenced
comments: Provide a numerical value (no need to include units).

consensus genome length.name: consensus genome length
consensus genome length.description: Size of the reconstructed genome described as the number of base pairs.
consensus genome length.title: consensus genome length
comments: Provide a numerical value (no need to include units).

reference genome accession.name: reference genome accession
reference genome accession.description: A persistent, unique identifier of a genome database entry.
reference genome accession.title: reference genome accession
comments: Provide the accession number of the reference genome.

bioinformatics protocol.name: bioinformatics protocol
bioinformatics protocol.description: A description of the overall bioinformatics strategy used.
bioinformatics protocol.title: bioinformatics protocol
comments: Further details regarding the methods used to process raw data, and/or generate assemblies, and/or generate consensus sequences can. This information can be provided in an SOP or protocol or pipeline/workflow. Provide the name and version number of the protocol, or a GitHub link to a pipeline or workflow.

gene name 1.name: gene name 1
gene name 1.description: The name of the gene used in the diagnostic RT-PCR test.
gene name 1.title: gene name 1
comments: Provide the full name of the gene used in the test. The gene symbol (short form of gene name) can also be provided. Standardized gene names and symbols can be found in the Gene Ontology using this look-up service: https://bit.ly/2Sq1LbI

diagnostic pcr Ct value 1.name: diagnostic pcr Ct value 1
diagnostic pcr Ct value 1.description: The Ct value result from a diagnostic SARS-CoV-2 RT-PCR test.
diagnostic pcr Ct value 1.title: diagnostic pcr Ct value 1
comments: Provide the CT value of the sample from the diagnostic RT-PCR test.

gene name 2.name: gene name 2
gene name 2.description: The name of the gene used in the diagnostic RT-PCR test.
gene name 2.title: gene name 2
comments: Provide the full name of another gene used in an RT-PCR test. The gene symbol (short form of gene name) can also be provided. Standardized gene names and symbols can be found in the Gene Ontology using this look-up service: https://bit.ly/2Sq1LbI

diagnostic pcr Ct value 2.name: diagnostic pcr Ct value 2
diagnostic pcr Ct value 2.description: The Ct value result from a diagnostic SARS-CoV-2 RT-PCR test.
diagnostic pcr Ct value 2.title: diagnostic pcr Ct value 2
comments: Provide the CT value of the sample from the second diagnostic RT-PCR test.

gene name 3.name: gene name 3
gene name 3.description: The name of the gene used in the diagnostic RT-PCR test.
gene name 3.title: gene name 3
comments: Provide the full name of another gene used in an RT-PCR test. The gene symbol (short form of gene name) can also be provided. Standardized gene names and symbols can be found in the Gene Ontology using this look-up service: https://bit.ly/2Sq1LbI

diagnostic pcr Ct value 3.name: diagnostic pcr Ct value 3
diagnostic pcr Ct value 3.description: The Ct value result from a diagnostic SARS-CoV-2 RT-PCR test.
diagnostic pcr Ct value 3.title: diagnostic pcr Ct value 3
comments: Provide the CT value of the sample from the second diagnostic RT-PCR test.

authors.name: authors
authors.description: Names of individuals contributing to the processes of sample collection, sequence generation, analysis, and data submission.
authors.title: authors
comments: Include the first and last names of all individuals that should be attributed, separated by a comma.

examples.value: Tejinder Singh, Fei Hu, Joe Blogs

DataHarmonizer provenance.name: DataHarmonizer provenance
DataHarmonizer provenance.description: The DataHarmonizer software and template version provenance.
DataHarmonizer provenance.title: DataHarmonizer provenance
comments: The current software and template version information will be automatically generated in this field after the user utilizes the "validate" function. This information will be generated regardless as to whether the row is valid of not.
